{"title":"Week 1: Topic Selection and Research","markdown":{"headingText":"Week 1: Topic Selection and Research","containsRefs":false,"markdown":"\n## Objectives\nBy the end of this week, students will:\n\n- Have a quick recap of the goal of the course to get new students on board\n- Be introduced to potential pitfalls in Cognitive Neuroscience research\n- Select their preferred topics\n- Be assigned to groups based on their preferences\n\n## Milestones and Delivery Dates\nWe'll review the project milestones and their expected delivery dates. This will help you plan your work and ensure you stay on track throughout the course.\n\n## A Skeptical Approach to Cognitive Neuroscience Research\nIn this section, we'll discuss common pitfalls and areas of caution in Cognitive Neuroscience research. This \"skeptical watchlist\" will help you approach your research with a critical eye and ensure the scientific integrity of your podcast content.\n\nYou can find the slides for this section below.\n\n<iframe src=\"https://docs.google.com/presentation/d/e/2PACX-1vS1OwH5ZgBDFa9Lh_dBNbF7Giw9otT69rhwGYGfhJwtr8mqX7LjyGRRB8WyynTiBBlVYGstB531GN0T/embed?start=false&loop=false&delayms=5000\" frameborder=\"0\" width=\"960\" height=\"569\" allowfullscreen=\"true\" mozallowfullscreen=\"true\" webkitallowfullscreen=\"true\"></iframe>\n\n## Tasks\n1. Review the available topics and associated papers.\n2. Consider your interests and rate your preferences for the different topics.\n\n\n## Next Steps\nIn the coming weeks, you'll dive deeper into your chosen topic, conduct in-depth research, and begin planning your podcast episode. Start thinking about what aspects of your topic you find most intriguing and what questions you'd like to explore further.","srcMarkdownNoYaml":""},"formats":{"html":{"identifier":{"display-name":"HTML","target-format":"html","base-format":"html"},"execute":{"fig-width":7,"fig-height":5,"fig-format":"retina","fig-dpi":96,"df-print":"default","error":false,"eval":true,"